  "text": "I (x t , y t + k |y t ) or I (y t , x t + k |x t ) are closely related to the statistic termed transfer entropy, a measure of the deviation from the independence property for coupled systems evolving in time [CITATION_1] . It can be shown that under proper conditions the transfer entropy is equivalent to the conditional mutual information :",
